<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5372] Table mutation operations should check table level rights, not global rights </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5372</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;drop/modify/disable/enable etc table operations should not check for global CREATE/ADMIN rights, but table CREATE/ADMIN rights. Since we check for global permissions first for table permissions, configuring table access using global permissions will continue to work. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
